      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VALIDATE (1) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 7 lengths at Q Lakeside in a handy 24.84 beating Shamrock Hayze. Boasts a strong record from this draw with six wins and four minor placings from 11 starts. Looks to have an edge on most of these. FIRE ME UP (3) ran below his best last time finishing fifth (28.00) over 484m at Casino in a NG. Has a strong winning record at this journey. Some good form is emerging from his last run. In the mix. HEROIC FEDERER (7) skirted wide from an outside draw last start and found the front, leading throughout to win (23.08) at Casino in a Grade 4 over 411m. Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break from out wide. Has definite claims. DRINK TINS (2) is a last-start placegetter who is in the mix again.",
